	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65327503"><p><div class="quote"><p>Isn't consumption the problem, rather than production?</p></div><p>Big Oil has spent a lot of money making us dependent on oil. Are we all complicit? Not those of us with little to no decision making power, and especially not if we voted for something better.</p><p><div class="quote"><p>We're not going to get off oil, IMHO. Isn't it the most financially valuable resource on the planet (excluding real estate - maybe)?</p></div><p>The most financially valuable resource on the planet is farmland, it just isn't obvious enough yet because the effects of the fossil fuel industry are only really ramping up now. Additional energy in the chaotic system of climate and weather means less food security. Three meals away from a revolution...</p></div>
	</div>

